His-tagged proteins pulled down with TALON cobalt-chelating Sepharose resin.

Using an IRES derived from poliovirus, plasmids were designed to coexpress p180 and p68 and also p54 and p46. These are then suitable for the transfection of three or four subunits simultaneously because all of the cells expressing p180 will contain p68 and all of the cells expressing p54 will contain p46 at constant ratios.
